      • isEndOfStream

        public boolean isEndOfStream()
        Description copied from interface: HttpObject
        Gets whether the stream should be ended when writing this object. This can be useful for HttpHeaders-only responses or to more efficiently close the stream along with the last piece of HttpData. This only has meaning for HttpObject writers, not readers.
